parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt can cause engine damage, including damage to the valve train, rod bearings, and oil pump, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
Engine oil leaks can cause damage to the engine and surrounding components, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing the engine to fail.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the valve cover
causing oil to drip onto the ground or onto other engine components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine and surrounding components.
symptoms: The water pump leaks or fails
and potentially leading to engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the piston pin can cause engine damage, including damage to the cylinder walls and piston rings, leading to costly repairs.
Engine seizure can cause complete engine failure, leaving the driver stranded and requiring costly repairs.
symptoms: potentially causing damage to the engine and surrounding components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PCV valve can cause the engine to pump oil, leading to damage to the valve train and rod bearings.

the seat belt does not lock into place
the seat belt continues to tighten around the occupant
the seat belt does not stay fastened.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt to properly restrain the occupant can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.

the seat belt does not properly restrain the occupant

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning seat belt harness can cause injuries or fatalities by constricting the occupant or failing to provide adequate restraint in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt harness continues to tighten around the occupant
the seat belt harness causes injuries or fatalities.
